The Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, have fixed Wednesday, 12th January, 2022 to carry out the screening of aspirants for the Osun State governorship election primary. The party had initially fixed Tuesday, 11th January, 2022 for the screening of the aspirants by the party. A statement issued by Umar M. Nature, the National Organising Secretary of the Party, explained that the screening exercise had been set to begin 10 a.m. at the PDP National Secretariat, Abuja. Osun APC To Party’s National Reconciliation Committee:… Lagos Will Always Remember Fallen Heroes, Heroines –… According to him, the party regrets any inconveniences the change in date may have caused. The statement read, “All aspirants, leaders, critical stakeholders and members of our party in Osun State should take note and by this, guided accordingly.”